{"word":"συνήορος","slug":"συνήορος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>συνήορος</b></el> <el>(συνήορος, <el>doric and attic</el> <el>συνάορος, ον</el>,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:συναείρω'><el>συναείρω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>linked with, accompanying</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>joined in wedlock</i>, and as <a href='S:Substantive'>Subst.</a> <i>a consort</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}